From e1c9866173c5f8521f2d0768547a01508cb9ff27 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tuo Li <islituo@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 6 Jan 2026 11:24:28 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] dmaengine: idxd: fix possible wrong descriptor completion in llist_abort_desc()
Git-commit: e1c9866173c5f8521f2d0768547a01508cb9ff27
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc6
References: CVE-2026-31436 bsc#1262602

[ backport note: in this branch the failure was introduced in
    patches.suse/dmaengine-idxd-rework-descriptor-free-path-on-failur.patch
  as it had to carry the fixes from the commit aa8d18becc0c, as the
  upstream resolved by merge -- tiwai ]

At the end of this function, d is the traversal cursor of flist, but the
code completes found instead. This can lead to issues such as NULL pointer
dereferences, double completion, or descriptor leaks.

Fix this by completing d instead of found in the final
list_for_each_entry_safe() loop.

Fixes: aa8d18becc0c ("dmaengine: idxd: add callback support for iaa crypto")
Signed-off-by: Tuo Li <islituo@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Dave Jiang <dave.jiang@intel.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260106032428.162445-1-islituo@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Vinod Koul <vkoul@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/dma/idxd/submit.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/dma/idxd/submit.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/idxd/submit.c
@@ -135,7 +135,7 @@ static void llist_abort_desc(struct idxd
 	 */
 	list_for_each_entry_safe(d, t, &flist, list) {
 		list_del_init(&d->list);
-		idxd_dma_complete_txd(found, IDXD_COMPLETE_ABORT, true);
+		idxd_dma_complete_txd(d, IDXD_COMPLETE_ABORT, true);
 	}
 }
 
